<subSubSection id="C3196578FF92FFC35CB1FD0E8DD90EC5" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBC36F3FF92FFC35CB1FD0E8DD90EC5" blockId="3.[174,1233,341,767]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized from the combination of dorsally microtrichose costal cell, orbital setae very short, not differing from other setulae of frons, frons and anterior fronto-orbital plates yellow, postpronotal, presutural supra-alar, and katepisternal setae lacking; antenna and usually fore coxa yellow.</paragraph>
